New Records: New Zealand registered their first win against Australia in Australia in any format since 2011.
Key Match Events: Devon Conway scored an unbeaten 92 off 58 balls with seven fours and two sixes.
New Zealand posted a total of 200-3.
Finn Allen hit 42 off just 16 balls.
Mitchell Santner and Tim Southee both took three wickets each.
David Warner was dismissed for three runs in the second over.
Aaron Finch hit a giant six but was dismissed shortly after for 13.
Tim David was dismissed for 11, leaving Australia at 68-5 in the 11th over.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was a repeat of the 2021 final in Dubai where Australia won.
The match was held at a sold-out Sydney Cricket Ground.
